TerraClim data

AOI = getAOI(clip = LOR)
p = AOI %>% getTerraClim(param = c('tmax','tmin'), startDate = "2017-10-28")
r = raster::stack(p$tmax, p$tmin)
names(r) = c('tmax', 'tmin')
r <- raster::mask(r, LOR)
rasterVis::levelplot(r)

e = AOI %>% getTerraClim(param = c('q','prcp'), startDate = "2017-10-28")
r2 = raster::stack(e$q, e$prcp)
names(r2) = c('Runoff', 'prcp')
r2 <- raster::mask(r2, LOR)
rasterVis::levelplot(r2)

FUNCTIONS to climate data extraction and visualization

devtools::source_gist("3ca747e7d7a7ed2658257b71b4685bc8")
  1. clim_dat function to extract data from TerraClimate in sf format

Arguments:

shp shapefile or sf object of the AOI boundaries

par list of parameters to be extracted from TerraClim. Valid options include: aet, water_deficit, palmer, pet, prcp, q, soilm, srad, swe, tmax, tmin, vp, vpd, wind

fun function passed on directly to raster::extract

start start date for pulling TerraClimate data. Default=2000-01-01

end end date for pulling TerraClimate data. Default=2017-12-01

  1. filled.contour.tidy function to plot 2d contour surfaces tidyverse format

Arguments:

dat dataset

month variable name for month scale

year variable name for year scale

var attribute name

hline yintercept values passed on directly to geom_hline

palette palette name passed on directly to scale_fill_distiller

trans name of a scale transformation passed on directly to scale_fill_distiller

log1 wether var be transformed to log10

dire direction of scale passed on directly to scale_fill_distiller

PROCESSING TerraClim data (multiple parameters / multiple dates)

p<-c('tmax', 'tmin')
names(p) <- p #Important

clim_dt <- p %>%
  purrr::map(~clim_dat(shp=LOR, ., end="2000-03-01")) %>%
  bind_rows( .id = "var") %>%
  ungroup()

# Data wrangling
clim_dt_long <- clim_dt %>%
  dplyr::select(NAME_3, var, starts_with("X")) %>% #Change name of the ID-spatial unit (NAME_3)
  gather(date, value, -NAME_3, -var, -geometry) %>%
  spread(var,value) %>%
  mutate(date=str_remove_all(date,"X")) %>%
  separate(date,c("year","month"))

#Ploting
clim_dt_long %>% 
  ggplot() + 
  geom_sf(aes(fill=tmin), size = 0.3, col = "black") +
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "RdBu") +
  theme_void()  +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(color = "white"),
        strip.text = element_text(size=15)) +
  facet_wrap(.~month, nrow = 1, ncol = 3)

PROCESSING TerraClim data (single parameters / multiple dates) [Entire Region]

LOR.reg <- gadm_sp_loadCountries("PER", level=1, basefile="./") %>%
  gadm_subset(level = 1, regions="Loreto")
LOR.reg<-st_as_sf(LOR.reg$spdf)

LOR.prcp <- clim_dat(LOR.reg, par = "prcp", start="2000-01-01", end="2017-12-01")

# Data wrangling
LOR.prcp_long <- LOR.prcp %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  dplyr::select(NAME_1, starts_with("X")) %>% #Change name of the ID-spatial unit (NAME_3)
  gather(date, prcp, -NAME_1) %>%
  mutate(date=str_remove_all(date,"X")) %>%
  separate(date,c("YEAR","MONTH")) %>%
  mutate_at(c("YEAR","MONTH"), as.numeric)

CONTOUR.PLOT - TIDY

filled.contour.tidy(LOR.prcp_long, MONTH, YEAR, prcp, palette = "BrBG", dire = 1, log1 = F)
